org.finra.jtaf.ewd.impl

Class DefaultExtWebDriver

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.finra.jtaf.ewd.impl.DefaultExtWebDriver
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ExtWebDriver, HighlightProvider, org.openqa.selenium.SearchContext, org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver

    public class DefaultExtWebDriver
extends java.lang.Object
implements ExtWebDriver, HighlightProvider
    DefaultExtWebDriver is the default implementation of the ExtWebDriver interface to support more advanced window and frame handling on top of WebDriver

      • getGeneratedHtmlSource

        public java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> getGeneratedHtmlSource()
        Description copied from interface: ExtWebDriver
        Retrieves current state of the DOM in HTML format for each of the document's frames.
        Specified by:
        getGeneratedHtmlSource in interface ExtWebDriver
        Returns:
        A map of HTMLs. Each key describes the location of the FRAME relative to the root DOM. The value is the HTML associated with the key. A key example is FRAME[root-2-1], which identifies the IFRAME that is the 1st IFRAME found underneath the 2nd IFRAME underneath the root DOM.
